name: CNN
text:
Amazon CEO Jeff Bezos is opening the doors of his first preschool, the Bezos Academy.

It's the first location of a network of tuition-free preschools serving children in underserved communities spearheaded by Bezos' philanthropic arm, Day One Fund. https://t.co/1PVVwL3YVZ

name: CNN
text: Plumber Judaline Cassidy is encouraging girls to follow in her footsteps through her "Tools and Tiaras" program. She runs camps, monthly workshops and mentoring programs that introduce girls to construction trades like plumbing, carpentry and electrical. https://t.co/NfIDRexlzK https://t.co/z51EOnWlIl

text: Three railroad workers were suspended for building a man cave under Grand Central Terminal in New York. The room included a wall-mounted TV and streaming device, futon, air mattress, refrigerator and microwave, Metropolitan Transportation Authority says. https://t.co/9echkWuq6U

text: Mark Cuban is once again pushing the idea that every US household should receive $1,000 bi-weekly stimulus checks for the next two months. He suggests a "use or lose it" approach, where recipients must spend the funds within 10 days or they lose the money. https://t.co/hkFllDLFI0
